Interface I_WordNet

    Author:
    TEWatson Interface for accessing WordNet functionality

    • Method Detail

      • getSynonyms

        java.util.Set<java.lang.String> getSynonyms(CASSWordSense sense)
        Returns synonyms that correspond to the sense provided in the argument.

        The synonyms are returned as a Set of Strings, not CASSWordSenses, so the synonyms returned may themselves represent many different senses.

        Parameters:
        sense - CASSWordSense object for which to retrieve synonyms
        Returns:
        Set of Strings which are the synonyms of the given word sense

      • getSenses

        java.util.Set<CASSWordSense> getSenses(java.lang.String word)
        Returns all senses that may use the lemma provided in the argument.

        It is assumed that the word String entered is the lemmatized version of the word, or else no senses may be found the this query.

        Parameters:
        word - String lemma of the word being queried
        Returns:
        Set of CASSWordSense objects which share a lemma with the argument

      • getDefinition

        java.lang.String getDefinition(CASSWordSense sense)
        Returns the definition of the word sense provided in the argument.
        Parameters:
        sense - CASSWordSense object for which to retrieve a gloss
        Returns:
        String representation of the gloss

      • getHypernyms

        java.util.Set<CASSWordSense> getHypernyms(CASSWordSense sense)
        Returns all hypernyms of the argument according to WordNet.

        Depending on the WordNet used, this may or may not return any hypernyms for adjectives and adverbs. English WordNet does not return hypernyms for adjectives and adverbs.

        Parameters:
        sense - CASSWordSense object for which to retreive hypernyms
        Returns:
        Set of CASSWordSense objects which are hypernyms of the argument
